# Jenkins + Tomcat Deployment Project on AWS EC2

## 📌 Project Overview
This project demonstrates how to set up a complete CI/CD environment using **Jenkins**, **Tomcat**, and **AWS EC2**.  
A Jenkins controller was configured on a local WSL machine, and a remote Linux agent (`Linux-slave`) was connected through SSH to automate deployment tasks.

The project simulates a real-world DevOps workflow where code can be built and deployed to Apache Tomcat hosted on an EC2 instance.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

Developer → Jenkins (WSL Laptop) → Remote Jenkins Agent (AWS EC2) → Apache Tomcat Server

