## 🚀 Steps Implemented

### 1️⃣ Jenkins Installation on WSL
- Installed Jenkins on Ubuntu WSL
- Accessed Jenkins UI on browser using port `8080`

### 2️⃣ EC2 Instance Setup
- Launched Linux EC2 instance in AWS Mumbai region
- Configured Security Group rules:
  - SSH (22)
  - Tomcat Port (8080)

### 3️⃣ Jenkins Agent Configuration
- Created Jenkins node named `Linux-slave`
- Connected via SSH using PEM key authentication
- Configured remote workspace:
```bash
/home/ec2-user/jenkins
4️⃣ Tomcat Installation on EC2

Installed and configured Apache Tomcat.

5️⃣ Node Troubleshooting Performed

Resolved real-time issues such as:

SSH Authentication failure
Wrong username/key mismatch
Permission denied on /var/jenkins
Jenkins node offline due to /tmp low disk threshold
Increased /tmp tmpfs size from 480MB to 2GB
6️⃣ Deployment Ready Setup

Jenkins agent now ready to deploy WAR files into Tomcat webapps folder.

